text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Alabama took place on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump and his running mate Vice President Mike Pence had won 9 electoral votes in the Electoral college. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:21st century in Alabama
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Alabama
